Definition: Given short utterances from conversational domain pertaining to alarms, emails, or transportaion, classify the intent of the input into one of the following 11 labels: alarm_query, alarm_remove, alarm_set, email_addcontact, email_query, email_querycontact, email_sendemail, transport_query, transport_taxi, transport_ticket, or transport_traffic

Positive Examples.input: olly find any alarms i have set for today
Positive Examples.explanation: The message is a question and the subject is an alarm, so the intent is alarm_query
The yoga alarm is being removed, so the intent is alarm_remove
An alarm is being set, so the intent is alarm_set

Positive Examples.input: add Steve's email to my contacts
Positive Examples.explanation: They want to add an email to contacts, so the intent is email_addcontact

Positive Examples.input: i want to know if i have any emails with the subject line budget from eddie richards
Positive Examples.explanation: The message is a question and the subject is about emails, so the intent is  email_query

Positive Examples.input: how can i contact this person
Positive Examples.explanation: The message is a question and the subject is about emails and contacts, so the intent is email_querycontact

Positive Examples.input: send an email to rae telling her my phone is back in service
Positive Examples.explanation: They want to send an email to a person named rae, so the intent is email_sendemail

Positive Examples.input: when does the last train from work leave
Positive Examples.explanation: The message is a questiom and the subject is about transportation, so the intent is transport_query

Positive Examples.input: could you please book me a taxi going to location
Positive Examples.explanation: The message is about taxis, so the intent is transport_taxi

Positive Examples.input: book ticket to depart in the morning
Positive Examples.explanation: They message deals with tickets and transportation, so the intent is transport_ticket
The message is asking a question about traffic, so the intent is transport_traffic

Negative Examples.explanation: The message does not want to remove an alarm, it's asking a question. The correct intent is alarm_query
The message does not want to set any alarms, it wants to remove alarms. The correct intent is alarm_remove

Negative Examples.input: set alarm for sixth of june two thousand seventeen at five am
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is not asking a question, it wants to set an alarm. The correct intent is alarm_query

Negative Examples.input: add jan@gmail.com to my list of contacts
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is about contacts, but it is not asking any questions. The correct intent is email_addcontact

Negative Examples.input: did i have any new email
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is asking a question about emails, it is not about sending emails. The correct intent is email_query

Negative Examples.input: do i have any missed call from patrick
Negative Examples.explanation: The message does not want to add any contacts, it is asking about a contact. The correct intent is email_addcontact

Negative Examples.input: send an email to bill that i'm sorry i didn't realize he was so sick
Negative Examples.explanation: The message wants to send an email, it is not asking a question. The correct intent is email_sendemail

Negative Examples.input: tell me the train ticket price of california to chicago
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is inquiring about transportation and not traffic. The correct intent is transport_query

Negative Examples.input: 'book an uber to pick me up outside of long island bar right now
Negative Examples.explanation: The intent is asking for a taxi because uber is a type of taxi. It is not asking for a ticket. The correct intent is transport_taxi

Negative Examples.input: book ticket for paris by train
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is not about taxis, it wants to book tickets. The correct intent is transport_ticket

Negative Examples.input: are the streets congested right now
Negative Examples.explanation: The message is asking about traffic, not general transportation. The correct intent is transport_traffic
